Title: State of the Unification Address

Authors: M. J. Duff

Comments: 16 pages, Latex. Plenary talk delivered at The Division of Particles

and Fields Meeting of The American Physical Society, August 9-12 2000, OhioState University. Minor corrections and references addedJournal-ref: Int.J.Mod.Phys. A16S1A (2001) 77-91

After reviewing how M-theory subsumes string theory, I report on some new andtheorems for supersymmetric brane-worlds, complementarity of the Maldacena andRandall-Sundrum pictures; self-tuning of the cosmological constant. I concludewith the top ten unsolved problems.